overview: Sylt - the exceptional island where the "rich and beautiful" cavort in luxury boutiques and unaffordable villas, the jet set celebrates wild parties and the locals can barely afford to live. These are the clichés that many people associate with the North Sea island. Judith Rakers gets to know the island through the people she meets there. She explores the magic of contrasts with them.
title: Sylt … mit Judith Rakers
